@startuml
title Public recipe discovery - exact function calls

actor User
participant "HomePage" as HomePage
participant "updateFilters()" as UpdateFilters
participant "useRecipesQuery()" as UseRecipesQuery
participant "fetchRecipes()" as FetchRecipes
participant "fetchRecipesHttp()" as FetchRecipesHttp
participant "buildRecipeCollectionUrl()" as BuildCollectionUrl
participant "buildApiUrl()" as BuildApiUrl
participant "Program.cs\nMapGet(/api/recipes)" as RecipesEndpoint
participant "RecipeService.GetPublishedRecipes()" as GetPublishedRecipes
participant "EfRecipeRepository.GetAll()" as RepoGetAll

== Initial page load ==
User -> HomePage : Open /?search&category
HomePage -> UseRecipesQuery : useRecipesQuery({ search, category })
UseRecipesQuery -> FetchRecipes : fetchRecipes(filters)
FetchRecipes -> FetchRecipesHttp : fetchRecipesHttp(filters)
FetchRecipesHttp -> BuildCollectionUrl : buildRecipeCollectionUrl("/api/recipes", filters)
BuildCollectionUrl -> BuildApiUrl : buildApiUrl("/api/recipes")
BuildApiUrl --> BuildCollectionUrl : absolute URL
BuildCollectionUrl --> FetchRecipesHttp : URL with search params
FetchRecipesHttp -> RecipesEndpoint : GET /api/recipes?search&category
RecipesEndpoint -> GetPublishedRecipes : GetPublishedRecipes(search, category)
GetPublishedRecipes -> RepoGetAll : GetAll()
RepoGetAll --> GetPublishedRecipes : Recipe[]
GetPublishedRecipes --> RecipesEndpoint : List<RecipeResponse>
RecipesEndpoint --> FetchRecipesHttp : 200 OK + JSON
FetchRecipesHttp --> FetchRecipes : RecipeDetail[]
FetchRecipes --> UseRecipesQuery : query data
UseRecipesQuery --> HomePage : recipesQuery.data
HomePage --> User : Render discovery recipe cards

== User changes filters ==
User -> HomePage : Type search or select category
HomePage -> UpdateFilters : updateFilters({ search/category })
UpdateFilters -> HomePage : setSearchParams(nextParams)
HomePage -> UseRecipesQuery : useRecipesQuery({ search, category })

@enduml
